data.name: smoothLabel8.HelpText
data.value: This is the period of time in seconds that CallButler will re-register with the VoIP provider. This should usually be set to a lower value like 20-30 seconds if you have a NAT router or firewall connecting you to the Internet.

data.name: lblSipRegistration.HelpText
data.value: Most VoIP providers require SIP registration in order to receive inbound calls. However if you know for certain that your VoIP provider doesn't require SIP registration you may turn this off to cut down on network traffic.

data.name: smoothLabel7.HelpText
data.value:
Specify the SIP registrar server given to you by your provider. In most cases this is the same value as your domain/realm and proxy server. This value is usually similar in form to sip.domain.com.
This field will be used as the "sip.domain.com" paremeter when sent as a URI in SIP messages. Example: "Display Name" <sip:username@sip.domain.com>

data.name: smoothLabel6.HelpText
data.value:
Specify the SIP proxy server given to you by your provider. In many cases this may be the same value as your domain/realm and proxy server. This value is usually similar in form to sip.domain.com.
This field will be used as the "sip.domain.com" paremeter when sent as a URI in SIP messages. Example: "Display Name" <sip:username@sip.domain.com>

data.name: smoothLabel5.HelpText
data.value:
Specify the Domain or Realm given to you by your provider. In many cases this may be the same value as your proxy server and proxy server. This value is usually similar in form to sip.domain.com.
This field will be used as the "sip.domain.com" paremeter when sent as a URI in SIP messages. Example: "Display Name" <sip:username@sip.domain.com>

data.name: wizardHeader2.Description
data.value: Please enter the network settings used to connect to your provider

data.name: label3.Text
data.value: Testing VoIP Provider Connection. This test may take a few moments.

data.name: label1.Text
data.value: Here you may run a quick test to determine if the settings you used for your VoIP provider are correct. To begin the test, press the Begin Connection Test link below.

data.name: wizardHeader4.Description
data.value: Test the connection to your VoIP provider and make sure your settings were properly entered.

data.name: smoothLabel4.HelpText
data.value: Specify the password given to you by your provider.

data.name: smoothLabel3.HelpText
data.value: Specify the authorization username given to you by your provider. In most cases this is the EXACT same value used for your Telephone or Username setting in the previous page.

data.name: wizardHeader3.Description
data.value: Please enter your credentials for connecting to your provider

data.name: lblEnableProvider.HelpText
data.value: Check this if you want to accept incoming calls from this provider.

data.name: smoothLabel2.HelpText
data.value:
Specify the telephone number or username given to you by your provider. In most cases this is your telephone number (without any punctuation or spaces), but some providers may assign you a specific username.
This field will be used as the "username" paremeter when sent as a URI in SIP messages. Example: "Display Name" <sip:username@domain.com>

data.name: smoothLabel1.HelpText
data.value:
Specify the name you want callers to see when you make calls from CallButler. Normally this can be anything you want, but some VoIP providers may require you to use a specific value.
This field will be used as the "Display Name" paremeter when sent as a URI in SIP messages. Example: "Display Name" <sip:username@domain.com>
Note: Some VoIP providers may choose ignore this field and override your setting.

data.name: lblContinueCall.HelpText
data.value: Specify a name for this provider. This is used for your reference only and will not affect any settings for this provider.

data.name: wizardHeader1.Description
data.value: Please enter the providers name, caller id and telephone number
